Reasoning: The paper discusses performance evaluation of medium access schemes in wireless ad hoc networks, which falls under the category of network protocols and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses analytical tools and mathematical models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper mentions the average information rate received by a receiver node, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the comparison of different medium access schemes, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
